WEBVTT

851
00:00:01.706 --> 00:00:03.022
Though...

2
00:00:05.997 --> 00:00:07.858
I do not know the way

3
00:00:09.899 --> 00:00:13.183
I will help you bear this burden.
Frodo Baggins

4
00:00:13.877 --> 00:00:16.464
As long as this is yours to bear

5
00:00:18.882 --> 00:00:21.918
If by my life or death.
I can protect you.

6
00:00:22.732 --> 00:00:24.025
I will

7
00:00:27.437 --> 00:00:29.278
You have my sword

8
00:00:31.927 --> 00:00:33.867
And you have my bow

9
00:00:34.280 --> 00:00:35.782
And my axe

10
00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:46.378
You carry the fate of us all little one

11
00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:52.657
If this is indeed the will of the Council.

12
00:00:53.582 --> 00:00:55.663
then Gondor will see it done

13
00:00:55.664 --> 00:00:56.940
Hey!

14
00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:00.744
Mr. Frodo's not going
anywhere without me

15
00:01:00.745 --> 00:01:04.256
No. indeed. it is hardly possible to separate you.
even when he is

16
00:01:04.257 --> 00:01:07.196
summoned to a secret Council.
and you are not

17
00:01:08.954 --> 00:01:10.965
Hey! We're coming too!

18
00:01:12.533 --> 00:01:15.208
You'd have to send us home
tied up in a sack to stop us!

19
00:01:15.209 --> 00:01:18.896
Anyway. you need people of intelligence
on this sort of...

20
00:01:19.120 --> 00:01:20.488
Mission...

21
00:01:20.686 --> 00:01:21.962
Quest...

22
00:01:22.450 --> 00:01:23.934
Thing...

23
00:01:25.410 --> 00:01:28.175
Well that rules you out. Pip!

24
00:01:29.630 --> 00:01:31.009
Nine companions

25
00:01:33.219 --> 00:01:34.584
So be it!

26
00:01:35.121 --> 00:01:37.899
You shall be the Fellowship of the Ring

27
00:01:38.763 --> 00:01:39.987
Right!

28
00:01:40.785 --> 00:01:42.621
Where are we going?

29
00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:50.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

30
00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:55.595
My old sword. Sting

31
00:01:56.261 --> 00:01:58.537
Here. take it. take it!

32
00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:04.910
It's so light!

33
00:02:04.910 --> 00:02:07.680
Yes. yes� made by the Elves. you know?

34
00:02:07.945 --> 00:02:10.858
The blade glows blue when orcs are close.

35
00:02:12.256 --> 00:02:14.717
and it's at times like that. my lad.

36
00:02:14.718 --> 00:02:17.249
when you have to be extra careful

37
00:02:17.385 --> 00:02:19.343
Here's a pretty thing

38
00:02:20.258 --> 00:02:21.595
Mithril!

39
00:02:22.310 --> 00:02:24.413
As light as a feather.

40
00:02:24.462 --> 00:02:26.829
and as hard as dragon's scales

41
00:02:26.830 --> 00:02:29.011
Let me see you put it on

42
00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:35.677
Oh!... My old ring!

43
00:02:41.668 --> 00:02:43.111
I should...

44
00:02:43.910 --> 00:02:46.408
very much like
to hold it again.

45
00:02:46.814 --> 00:02:48.430
one last time

46
00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:10.546
I'm sorry I brought this upon you.
my boy

47
00:03:12.222 --> 00:03:15.924
I'm sorry that...
you must carry this burden

48
00:03:21.919 --> 00:03:24.564
I'm sorry for everything!

49
00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:39.266
We must hold to this course west of
the Misty Mountains for 40 days

50
00:04:39.267 --> 00:04:43.012
If our luck holds. the gap of Rohan
will still be open to us

51
00:04:44.116 --> 00:04:47.102
From there. our road turns east...
to Mordor

52
00:04:47.497 --> 00:04:49.203
2. 1. 5... Good!

53
00:04:49.819 --> 00:04:51.240
Very good!

54
00:04:53.080 --> 00:04:54.253
Move your feet!

55
00:04:54.253 --> 00:04:55.845
-You look good. Pippin!
-Thanks

56
00:04:55.847 --> 00:04:57.164
Faster!

57
00:04:58.952 --> 00:05:02.097
If anyone would ask for my opinion.
which I....

58
00:05:02.099 --> 00:05:05.076
I'd say we were taking the long way round

59
00:05:05.874 --> 00:05:09.194
Gandalf! We could pass
through the Mines of Moria

60
00:05:09.859 --> 00:05:12.983
My cousin Balin would give us
a royal welcome

61
00:05:13.845 --> 00:05:18.580
No. Gimli
I would not take the roads through Moria
unless I had no other choice

62
00:05:28.740 --> 00:05:30.466
Sorry!

63
00:05:31.022 --> 00:05:32.947
Get him!!

64
00:05:33.305 --> 00:05:34.940
For the Shire! Get him!

65
00:05:35.429 --> 00:05:36.737
Hold him. Hold him down!

66
00:05:36.737 --> 00:05:38.208
He got my arm. he got my arm�

67
00:05:38.210 --> 00:05:39.125
What is that?

68
00:05:39.125 --> 00:05:41.048
Nothing. it's just a wisp of cloud

69
00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:42.784
It's moving fast

70
00:05:43.740 --> 00:05:45.474
Against the wind

71
00:05:46.844 --> 00:05:48.085
Crebain from Dunland!

72
00:05:48.086 --> 00:05:49.290
Hide!

73
00:05:49.452 --> 00:05:50.848
Get down!

74
00:06:25.340 --> 00:06:27.163
Spies of Saruman!

75
00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:30.331
The passage south is being watched

76
00:06:31.694 --> 00:06:34.405
We must take the pass of Caradhras!

77
00:07:08.974 --> 00:07:10.310
Boromir!

78
00:07:11.436 --> 00:07:15.447
It is a strange fate that we
should suffer so much fear and doubt

79
00:07:15.950 --> 00:07:17.859
for so small a thing

80
00:07:22.310 --> 00:07:24.191
Such a little thing

81
00:07:24.383 --> 00:07:25.733
Boromir!

82
00:07:26.250 --> 00:07:28.324
Give the ring to Frodo!

83
00:07:38.898 --> 00:07:40.393
As you wish

84
00:07:41.385 --> 00:07:42.880
I care not!

85
00:08:19.330 --> 00:08:22.662
So Gandalf. you tried
to lead them over Caradhras

86
00:08:23.541 --> 00:08:25.353
And if that fails

87
00:08:26.277 --> 00:08:28.383
Where then will you go?

88
00:08:29.436 --> 00:08:31.788
If the mountain defeats you.

89
00:08:33.015 --> 00:08:35.857
will you risk the more dangerous road?

90
00:08:49.860 --> 00:08:52.450
There is a foul voice on the air

91
00:08:53.601 --> 00:08:55.295
It's Saruman!!

92
00:09:04.408 --> 00:09:07.108
He's trying to bring down the mountain!!

93
00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:09.062
Gandalf! We must turn back!

94
00:09:09.064 --> 00:09:10.209
No!

95
00:09:13.512 --> 00:09:16.700
Losto Caradhras
Sedho. hodo. nuitho i 'ruith!

96
00:09:23.365 --> 00:09:27.849
..Cuiva nwalca Carnirass�!
Nai yarvax�a rasselya! Talto notto-carinnar!

97
00:10:17.365 --> 00:10:21.150
We must get off the mountain! Make for the gap of Rohan!

98
00:10:22.062 --> 00:10:24.015
Or take the west road to White City!

99
00:10:24.016 --> 00:10:27.354
The Gap of Rohan
takes us too close to Isengard!

100
00:10:27.424 --> 00:10:30.957
If we cannot pass over the mountain.
let us go under it!

101
00:10:30.957 --> 00:10:33.747
Let us go through the Mines of Moria

102
00:10:36.279 --> 00:10:37.525
Moria!

103
00:10:37.526 --> 00:10:40.066
You fear to go into those mines

104
00:10:40.435 --> 00:10:43.573
The Dwarves dealt too greedily.
and too deep

105
00:10:46.671 --> 00:10:50.307
You know what they awoke
in the darkness of Khazad-dum

106
00:10:52.907 --> 00:10:54.849
Shadow and flame...

107
00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:02.041
Let the ring bearer decide...

108
00:11:07.665 --> 00:11:08.960
Frodo?

109
00:11:12.278 --> 00:11:14.669
We will go through the mines

110
00:11:15.979 --> 00:11:17.423
So be it!

111
00:11:25.997 --> 00:11:27.939
The walls of Moria!

112
00:11:40.006 --> 00:11:41.599
Let's see...

113
00:11:42.084 --> 00:11:43.528
Ithildin!

114
00:11:43.747 --> 00:11:46.636
It mirrors only
starlight and moonlight

115
00:12:01.539 --> 00:12:04.677
It reads: The doors of Durin. Lord of Moria

116
00:12:06.611 --> 00:12:08.702
Speak friend and enter

117
00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:10.893
What d' you suppose that means?

118
00:12:10.893 --> 00:12:11.930
Oh. it's quite simple

119
00:12:11.931 --> 00:12:16.171
If you're a friend. you speak the password.
and the doors will open

120
00:12:16.173 --> 00:12:18.614
Annon edhellen. edro hi ammen

121
00:12:36.666 --> 00:12:40.203
....Ando Eldarinwa a lasta quettanya
Fenda Casarinwa

122
00:12:46.477 --> 00:12:48.918
Mines are no place for a pony

123
00:12:49.678 --> 00:12:51.920
Even one so brave as Bill

124
00:12:52.463 --> 00:12:54.107
Bye bye! Bill

125
00:12:54.873 --> 00:12:56.815
Go on. Bill. Go on!

126
00:12:58.075 --> 00:13:00.865
Don't worry Sam
He knows the way home

127
00:13:08.343 --> 00:13:10.535
Do not disturb the water

128
00:13:25.596 --> 00:13:27.290
It's a riddle!

129
00:13:30.583 --> 00:13:32.825
Speak 'friend'. and enter

130
00:13:33.992 --> 00:13:36.681
What's the elvish word for friend?

131
00:13:38.274 --> 00:13:40.017
Humm?... Mellon

132
00:13:57.812 --> 00:14:01.996
Soon master Elf. you will enjoy fabled
hospitality of the dwarves

133
00:14:03.007 --> 00:14:06.195
Roaring fires! Malt beer!
Red meat of a bone!

134
00:14:10.366 --> 00:14:13.704
This. my friend. is the home of my cousin Balin

135
00:14:13.775 --> 00:14:15.967
And they call it a mine.

136
00:14:16.392 --> 00:14:17.736
A MINE!

137
00:14:19.552 --> 00:14:21.295
This is no mine

138
00:14:21.341 --> 00:14:22.934
It's a tomb!

139
00:14:31.691 --> 00:14:32.936
NO!!!

140
00:14:35.806 --> 00:14:37.200
Goblins!

141
00:14:41.086 --> 00:14:43.290
We make for the Gap of Rohan

142
00:14:43.291 --> 00:14:45.781
We should never have come here

143
00:14:46.905 --> 00:14:49.395
Now get out of here! Get out!!

144
00:15:37.705 --> 00:15:39.367
Into the mines!

145
00:15:39.367 --> 00:15:41.458
Legolas!
Into the cave!

146
00:16:05.516 --> 00:16:07.807
We now have but one choice

147
00:16:08.177 --> 00:16:10.917
We must face the long dark of Moria

148
00:16:13.539 --> 00:16:17.524
Be on your guard. There are older
and fouler things than orcs

149
00:16:19.774 --> 00:16:22.314
in the deep places of the world

150
00:16:31.081 --> 00:16:34.518
Quiet...
It's a four day journey to the other side

151
00:16:35.489 --> 00:16:38.726
Let us hope that our presence
may go unnoticed

152
00:17:25.746 --> 00:17:28.236
I have no memory of this place

153
00:17:30.526 --> 00:17:32.319
-Are we lost?
-No

154
00:17:32.606 --> 00:17:33.519
I think we are

155
00:17:33.520 --> 00:17:34.516
Shhhh... Gandalf is thinking!

156
00:17:34.518 --> 00:17:36.162
-Merry!
-What?

157
00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:37.675
I'm hungry

158
00:17:49.773 --> 00:17:52.164
There's something down there

159
00:17:52.602 --> 00:17:54.644
-It's Gollum!
-Gollum?

160
00:17:55.552 --> 00:17:58.192
He's been following us for 3 days

161
00:17:58.795 --> 00:18:01.585
He escaped the dungeons of Barad-Dur

162
00:18:01.954 --> 00:18:04.146
Escaped. Or set loose...

163
00:18:11.557 --> 00:18:13.898
He hates and loves the ring

164
00:18:14.716 --> 00:18:17.127
as he hates and loves himself

165
00:18:17.127 --> 00:18:19.869
He will never be rid of his need for it

166
00:18:19.869 --> 00:18:22.695
It's a pity Bilbo didn't kill him
when he had the chance

167
00:18:22.696 --> 00:18:23.941
Pity?

168
00:18:25.107 --> 00:18:27.897
It was pity that stayed Bilbo's hand

169
00:18:28.640 --> 00:18:31.031
Many that live deserve death

170
00:18:31.674 --> 00:18:33.965
Some that die deserve life

171
00:18:35.457 --> 00:18:37.997
Can you give it to them. Frodo?

172
00:18:39.862 --> 00:18:43.349
Do not be too eager to deal out
death and judgement

173
00:18:44.892 --> 00:18:47.731
Even the very wise
cannot see all ends

174
00:18:47.800 --> 00:18:51.536
My heart tells me that
Gollum has some part to play yet.

175
00:18:51.999 --> 00:18:54.789
for good or evil.
before this is over

176
00:18:58.983 --> 00:19:02.021
The pity of Bilbo
may rule the fate of men

177
00:19:09.622 --> 00:19:12.561
I wish the ring had never come to me...

178
00:19:14.819 --> 00:19:16.771
I wish none of this had happened...

179
00:19:16.772 --> 00:19:19.611
So do all who lives to see such times

180
00:19:19.640 --> 00:19:21.925
but that is not for them to decide.

181
00:19:21.926 --> 00:19:24.002
all we have to decide is

182
00:19:24.004 --> 00:19:27.142
what to do with the time
that is given to us

183
00:19:29.574 --> 00:19:33.523
There are other forces at work in this world
Frodo besides the will of evil

184
00:19:33.523 --> 00:19:36.113
Bilbo was meant to find the ring

185
00:19:36.724 --> 00:19:39.862
In which case you also were meant
to have it

186
00:19:40.755 --> 00:19:43.444
And that is an encouraging thought

187
00:19:48.943 --> 00:19:50.637
It's that way!

188
00:19:51.105 --> 00:19:52.019
He's remembered!

189
00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:53.183
No...

190
00:19:53.184 --> 00:19:56.504
But the air doesn't smell
so foul down here

191
00:19:58.187 --> 00:20:01.667
If in doubt. Meriadoc.
always follow your nose

192
00:20:20.170 --> 00:20:22.722
Let me risk a little more light

193
00:20:28.272 --> 00:20:29.723
The halls

194
00:20:30.944 --> 00:20:34.147
The great ground of dwarf city
of Dwarrowdelf

195
00:20:38.796 --> 00:20:41.398
There's an eye-opener no mistake

196
00:21:05.234 --> 00:21:06.385
No!

197
00:21:22.273 --> 00:21:23.424
No!

198
00:21:34.008 --> 00:21:36.560
Here lies Balin. son of Fundin.

199
00:21:38.728 --> 00:21:40.380
Lord of Moria

200
00:21:42.780 --> 00:21:44.532
He is dead then

201
00:21:46.162 --> 00:21:47.964
It's as I feared

202
00:21:58.107 --> 00:22:02.311
Kilmin malur ni zaram kalil ra narag.
Kheled-z�ram Balin tazlifi.

203
00:22:05.833 --> 00:22:08.485
We must move on. We cannot linger

204
00:22:09.591 --> 00:22:11.893
They have taken the bridge

205
00:22:12.013 --> 00:22:13.965
and the second hall

206
00:22:14.395 --> 00:22:16.396
We have barred gates

207
00:22:17.819 --> 00:22:20.271
but cannot hold them for long

208
00:22:20.617 --> 00:22:22.469
The ground shakes

209
00:22:23.876 --> 00:22:25.277
Drums...

210
00:22:25.671 --> 00:22:27.672
Drums in the deep...

211
00:22:32.897 --> 00:22:34.898
We cannot get out...

212
00:22:36.907 --> 00:22:39.359
A shadow moves in the dark...

213
00:22:42.085 --> 00:22:44.086
We cannot get out...

214
00:22:48.099 --> 00:22:50.001
They are coming...

215
00:23:32.745 --> 00:23:34.497
Fool of a Took!

216
00:23:35.542 --> 00:23:36.753
Throw yourself in next time.

217
00:23:36.754 --> 00:23:39.206
and rid us of your stupidity!

218
00:24:04.820 --> 00:24:06.121
Frodo!

219
00:24:08.872 --> 00:24:10.123
Orcs!

220
00:24:17.600 --> 00:24:20.202
Get back! Stay close to Gandalf!

221
00:24:26.662 --> 00:24:28.763
They have a cave troll

222
00:24:43.870 --> 00:24:48.325
Let them come! There is one dwarf yet
in Moria that still draws blood!

223
00:26:40.476 --> 00:26:42.428
..... hang of this!

224
00:26:47.576 --> 00:26:48.877
Frodo!

225
00:27:23.117 --> 00:27:24.202
Aragorn!

226
00:27:24.203 --> 00:27:25.604
Aragorn!

227
00:27:25.665 --> 00:27:26.966
Frodo!

228
00:28:12.608 --> 00:28:13.909
Frodo!

229
00:28:17.203 --> 00:28:18.504
Frodo!

230
00:29:24.819 --> 00:29:26.370
He's alive!

231
00:29:29.412 --> 00:29:31.764
I'm all right. I'm not hurt

232
00:29:31.961 --> 00:29:33.863
You should be dead

233
00:29:34.633 --> 00:29:37.639
That spear would have skewered a wild boar

234
00:29:37.640 --> 00:29:41.294
I think there's more to this hobbit
than meets the eye

235
00:29:48.289 --> 00:29:49.690
Mithril!

236
00:29:51.923 --> 00:29:54.876
You are full of surprises. Mr. Baggins!

237
00:30:00.526 --> 00:30:02.928
To the bridge of Khazad-Dum!

238
00:31:29.653 --> 00:31:31.905
What is this new devilry?

239
00:31:48.696 --> 00:31:50.147
A Balrog!

240
00:31:51.704 --> 00:31:54.156
A demon of the ancient world!

241
00:31:57.133 --> 00:31:59.635
This foe is beyond any of you!

242
00:32:00.724 --> 00:32:01.925
RUN!

243
00:32:28.330 --> 00:32:29.541
Gandalf!

244
00:32:29.543 --> 00:32:32.546
Lead them on Aragorn!
The bridge is near!

245
00:32:37.101 --> 00:32:38.702
Do as I say!

246
00:32:39.022 --> 00:32:41.424
Swords are no more use here!

247
00:33:10.346 --> 00:33:11.747
Gandalf!

248
00:33:30.350 --> 00:33:32.052
Merry! Pippin!

249
00:33:42.504 --> 00:33:43.705
Sam!

250
00:33:47.433 --> 00:33:49.534
Nobody tosses a dwarf!

251
00:33:53.656 --> 00:33:55.558
No! Not the beard!

252
00:34:47.156 --> 00:34:48.808
Lean forward!

253
00:35:13.258 --> 00:35:14.678
Over the bridge!

254
00:35:15.530 --> 00:35:16.722
Fly!

255
00:36:01.910 --> 00:36:03.712
You cannot pass!

256
00:36:03.956 --> 00:36:05.357
Gandalf!

257
00:36:10.139 --> 00:36:11.559
I am a servant of the Secret Fire.

258
00:36:11.560 --> 00:36:14.013
wielder of the flame of Anor!

259
00:36:15.445 --> 00:36:18.098
The dark fire will not avail you.

260
00:36:18.202 --> 00:36:19.904
flame of Udun!

261
00:36:29.484 --> 00:36:31.586
Go back to the shadow!

262
00:36:39.260 --> 00:36:41.202
YOU SHALL NOT PASS!

263
00:37:10.966 --> 00:37:12.709
No!
No! Gandalf!

264
00:37:22.144 --> 00:37:23.887
Fly. you fools!

265
00:37:37.809 --> 00:37:39.203
Aragorn!

266
00:38:36.650 --> 00:38:39.073
Legolas. get them up!

267
00:38:43.950 --> 00:38:46.166
Give them a moment for pity's sake

268
00:38:46.167 --> 00:38:49.319
By nightfall these hills
will be swarming with orcs

269
00:38:49.700 --> 00:38:52.554
We must reach the woods of Lothlorien

270
00:38:54.336 --> 00:38:57.390
Come Boromir. Legolas. Gimli!
Get them up!

271
00:38:57.888 --> 00:38:59.790
On your feet. Sam!

272
00:39:00.730 --> 00:39:02.081
Frodo?!

273
00:39:04.782 --> 00:39:06.083
Frodo!

274
00:39:59.394 --> 00:40:01.597
Stay close. you hobbits!

275
00:40:02.402 --> 00:40:05.957
They say that a great sorceress
lives in these woods

276
00:40:07.041 --> 00:40:08.693
An Elf witch.

277
00:40:09.839 --> 00:40:11.741
of terrible power!

278
00:40:13.224 --> 00:40:16.278
All who look upon her
fall under her spell

279
00:40:17.861 --> 00:40:19.162
Frodo!

280
00:40:21.664 --> 00:40:23.668
And are never seen again!

281
00:40:23.670 --> 00:40:26.975
Your coming to us.
is as the footsteps of doom!

282
00:40:28.474 --> 00:40:30.187
You bring great evil here.

283
00:40:30.188 --> 00:40:31.739
Ring-bearer

284
00:40:32.319 --> 00:40:33.820
Mr. Frodo?

285
00:40:39.798 --> 00:40:43.303
Well. here's one dwarf
she won't ensnare so easily!

286
00:40:45.147 --> 00:40:48.502
I have the eyes of a hawk
and the ears of a fox!

287
00:40:49.742 --> 00:40:50.893
Oh!

288
00:40:57.681 --> 00:41:01.787
The dwarf breathes so loud.
we could have shot him in the dark!

289
00:41:03.740 --> 00:41:05.201
Haldir o Lorien

290
00:41:05.202 --> 00:41:08.957
Henion aniron. boe ammen I dulu lin
Boe ammen veriad lin

291
00:41:11.679 --> 00:41:13.976
Aragorn! These woods are perilous!

292
00:41:13.977 --> 00:41:15.814
We should go back!

293
00:41:15.816 --> 00:41:18.864
You have entered the realm
of the Lady of the Wood

294
00:41:18.865 --> 00:41:20.767
You cannot go back

295
00:41:24.005 --> 00:41:25.256
Come.

296
00:41:25.466 --> 00:41:27.168
she is waiting

297
00:42:34.410 --> 00:42:38.559
Eight there are here.
yet nine there were set out from Rivendell

298
00:42:39.205 --> 00:42:43.254
Tell me. where is Gandalf.
for I much desire to speak with him

299
00:42:47.125 --> 00:42:49.374
He has fallen into shadow

300
00:42:55.505 --> 00:42:58.554
The quest stands upon the edge of a knife

301
00:42:59.132 --> 00:43:01.931
Stray but a little. and it will fail

302
00:43:02.716 --> 00:43:04.615
to the ruin of all

303
00:43:19.227 --> 00:43:21.076
Yet hope remains.

304
00:43:21.436 --> 00:43:23.485
while company is true

305
00:43:27.064 --> 00:43:28.980
Do not let your hearts be troubled.

306
00:43:28.981 --> 00:43:30.780
go now and rest.

307
00:43:31.942 --> 00:43:35.091
for you are weary with sorrow and much toil

308
00:43:37.779 --> 00:43:40.028
Tonight. you will sleep..

309
00:43:40.072 --> 00:43:42.471
Welcome. Frodo of the Shire.

310
00:43:44.824 --> 00:43:47.073
one who has seen the Eye!

311
00:44:01.582 --> 00:44:03.581
A lament for Gandalf

312
00:44:05.794 --> 00:44:08.193
What did they say about him?

313
00:44:08.254 --> 00:44:10.853
I have not the heart to tell you

314
00:44:11.548 --> 00:44:14.247
For me the grief is still too near

315
00:44:16.050 --> 00:44:17.749
Take some rest

316
00:44:18.760 --> 00:44:21.359
These borders are well protected

317
00:44:21.511 --> 00:44:23.710
I will find no rest here

318
00:44:26.639 --> 00:44:29.138
I heard a voice inside my head

319
00:44:30.141 --> 00:44:33.340
She spoke of my father
and the fall of Gondor

320
00:44:34.144 --> 00:44:37.243
She said to me.
even now there is hope left

321
00:44:40.938 --> 00:44:42.937
but I cannot see it!

322
00:44:45.357 --> 00:44:47.906
It's long since we had any hope

323
00:44:57.490 --> 00:44:59.739
My father is a noble man.

324
00:45:00.616 --> 00:45:02.765
but his rule if failing

325
00:45:03.868 --> 00:45:05.367
and our...

326
00:45:05.577 --> 00:45:07.626
Our people lose faith

327
00:45:10.496 --> 00:45:14.290
He looks to me to make things right.
and I. I would do it

328
00:45:14.291 --> 00:45:17.290
I would see the glory of Gondor restored

329
00:45:20.502 --> 00:45:23.051
Have you ever seen it. Aragorn?

330
00:45:24.046 --> 00:45:26.463
The white tower of Ecthelion?

331
00:45:26.464 --> 00:45:29.563
Glimmering like a spike
of pearl and silver

332
00:45:30.634 --> 00:45:33.883
It's banners caught high
in the morning breeze

333
00:45:37.012 --> 00:45:41.511
Have you ever been called home
by the clear ringing of silver trumpets?

334
00:45:43.973 --> 00:45:46.422
I have seen the White City...

335
00:45:47.434 --> 00:45:48.833
Long ago

336
00:45:49.936 --> 00:45:52.735
One day our paths will lead us there

337
00:45:55.648 --> 00:45:58.747
And the tower guard shall take up the call

338
00:45:59.190 --> 00:46:02.039
For the Lords of Gondor have returned

339
00:47:09.689 --> 00:47:12.188
Will you look into the mirror?

340
00:47:12.524 --> 00:47:14.323
What will I see?

341
00:47:16.984 --> 00:47:19.333
Even the wisest cannot tell

342
00:47:20.319 --> 00:47:22.918
For the mirror shows many things

343
00:47:27.865 --> 00:47:29.714
Things that were.

344
00:47:30.284 --> 00:47:32.083
things that are.

345
00:47:33.785 --> 00:47:35.534
and some things

346
00:47:39.121 --> 00:47:41.620
that have not yet come to pass

347
00:49:05.170 --> 00:49:07.419
I know what it is you saw

348
00:49:10.548 --> 00:49:12.797
For it is also in my mind

349
00:49:15.175 --> 00:49:18.474
It is what will come to pass
if you should fail

350
00:49:21.261 --> 00:49:23.560
The fellowship is breaking

351
00:49:24.222 --> 00:49:26.221
It has already begun

352
00:49:26.848 --> 00:49:29.247
He will try to take the ring

353
00:49:30.351 --> 00:49:32.550
You know of whom I speak

354
00:49:33.352 --> 00:49:34.901
One by one.

355
00:49:35.102 --> 00:49:37.301
it will destroy them all

356
00:49:39.396 --> 00:49:41.395
If you ask it of me.

357
00:49:42.398 --> 00:49:44.797
I will give you The One Ring

358
00:49:46.485 --> 00:49:48.734
You offer it to me freely

359
00:49:52.904 --> 00:49:56.453
I do not deny that my heart
has greatly desired this

360
00:50:03.160 --> 00:50:06.409
In place of a Dark Lord
you would have a Queen

361
00:50:07.371 --> 00:50:09.413
Not dark but beautiful

362
00:50:09.414 --> 00:50:11.613
and terrible as the dawn

363
00:50:11.706 --> 00:50:13.805
Treacherous as the sea

364
00:50:15.208 --> 00:50:18.307
Stronger than the foundations of the earth

365
00:50:20.628 --> 00:50:23.027
All shall love me
and despair

366
00:50:39.889 --> 00:50:41.638
I pass the test

367
00:50:42.724 --> 00:50:44.523
I will diminish.

368
00:50:44.976 --> 00:50:46.975
and go into the west

369
00:50:47.435 --> 00:50:49.434
and remain Galadriel

370
00:50:50.145 --> 00:50:52.244
I cannot do this alone

371
00:50:55.106 --> 00:50:57.505
You are a ring-bearer. Frodo

372
00:50:58.357 --> 00:51:01.206
To bear a ring of power
is to be alone

373
00:51:02.861 --> 00:51:05.410
This task was appointed to you.

374
00:51:05.904 --> 00:51:08.353
and if you do not find a way.

375
00:51:09.697 --> 00:51:11.246
no one will

376
00:51:13.158 --> 00:51:15.507
Then I know what I must do.

377
00:51:16.409 --> 00:51:17.908
it's just.

378
00:51:21.246 --> 00:51:23.195
I'm afraid to do it

379
00:51:26.999 --> 00:51:30.948
Even the smallest person
can change the course of the future

380
00:51:36.879 --> 00:51:40.178
Do you know how the orcs
first came into being?

381
00:51:44.009 --> 00:51:46.108
They were Elves. once.

382
00:51:48.052 --> 00:51:50.094
taken by the dark powers.

383
00:51:50.094 --> 00:51:52.243
tortured. and mutilated

384
00:51:56.098 --> 00:51:58.847
A ruined. and terrible form of life

385
00:52:01.435 --> 00:52:02.834
And now.

386
00:52:04.145 --> 00:52:05.644
perfected.

387
00:52:06.104 --> 00:52:08.103
my fighting Uruk-Hai

388
00:52:12.149 --> 00:52:14.048
Whom do you serve?

389
00:52:14.817 --> 00:52:16.166
Saruman

390
00:52:37.288 --> 00:52:38.788
Hunt them down!

391
00:52:38.789 --> 00:52:41.206
Do not stop until they are found!

392
00:52:41.207 --> 00:52:43.999
You do not know pain.
you do not know fear!

393
00:52:44.000 --> 00:52:46.249
You will taste man flesh!

394
00:52:52.129 --> 00:52:55.728
One of the Halflings carries
something of great value

395
00:52:56.256 --> 00:52:59.005
Bring them to me alive and unspoilt

396
00:53:02.594 --> 00:53:04.393
Kill the others!

397
00:53:31.652 --> 00:53:33.851
Farewell. Frodo Baggins!

398
00:53:34.320 --> 00:53:36.969
I give you the light of E�rendil.

399
00:53:38.531 --> 00:53:41.030
our most beloved star. Namarie

400
00:53:53.163 --> 00:53:56.212
May it be a light for you in dark places.

401
00:53:57.333 --> 00:53:59.782
where all other lights go out

402
00:55:40.390 --> 00:55:41.689
Frodo!

403
00:55:43.892 --> 00:55:45.491
The Argonath

404
00:55:48.311 --> 00:55:51.710
Long have I desired
to look upon the Kings of old

405
00:55:53.439 --> 00:55:54.738
My kin

406
00:57:14.360 --> 00:57:16.276
We cross the lake at nightfall

407
00:57:16.277 --> 00:57:19.076
Hide the boats. and continue on foot

408
00:57:19.486 --> 00:57:21.320
We approach Mordor from the north

409
00:57:21.321 --> 00:57:22.670
Oh yes?

410
00:57:23.155 --> 00:57:26.657
Just a simple matter
of finding our way through Emyn-Muil?

411
00:57:26.658 --> 00:57:29.857
An impassable labyrinth
of razor sharp rocks.

412
00:57:30.952 --> 00:57:33.751
and after that. it gets even better!

413
00:57:34.288 --> 00:57:38.287
The festering. stinking marshlands.
as far as the eye can see

414
00:57:39.498 --> 00:57:41.297
That is our road

415
00:57:42.375 --> 00:57:45.458
I suggest you take some rest
and recover your strength. Master Dwarf

416
00:57:45.459 --> 00:57:47.158
Recover my...!

417
00:57:50.379 --> 00:57:51.421
We should leave now

418
00:57:51.422 --> 00:57:54.121
No. Orcs patrol the eastern shore.

419
00:57:54.257 --> 00:57:56.956
we must wait for cover of darkness

420
00:57:57.384 --> 00:58:00.483
It is not the eastern shore
that worries me

421
00:58:00.509 --> 00:58:03.908
A shadow and a threat
has been growing in my mind

422
00:58:05.513 --> 00:58:07.512
Something draws near

423
00:58:07.514 --> 00:58:09.213
I can feel it!

424
00:58:11.224 --> 00:58:13.623
Ho. ho! Recover strength...!

425
00:58:13.642 --> 00:58:16.291
Pay no heed to that. young hobbit

426
00:58:16.644 --> 00:58:18.343
Where's Frodo?

427
00:58:44.242 --> 00:58:46.741
None of us should wander alone

428
00:58:47.202 --> 00:58:49.001
You least of all

429
00:58:50.038 --> 00:58:52.287
So much depends on you...

430
00:58:53.040 --> 00:58:54.339
Frodo?

431
00:59:01.960 --> 00:59:04.359
I know why you seek solitude

432
00:59:05.087 --> 00:59:07.636
You suffer. I see it day by day

433
00:59:10.090 --> 00:59:12.939
You sure you do not suffer needlessly

434
00:59:15.093 --> 00:59:17.442
There are other ways. Frodo

435
00:59:17.886 --> 00:59:19.178
Other paths that we might take

436
00:59:19.179 --> 00:59:20.720
I know what you would say.

437
00:59:20.721 --> 00:59:24.770
and it would seem like wisdom.
but for the warning in my heart

438
00:59:25.515 --> 00:59:27.614
Warning? Against what?

439
00:59:29.101 --> 00:59:31.300
We're all afraid. Frodo.

440
00:59:31.478 --> 00:59:35.327
but to let that fear drive us
to destroy what hope we have

441
00:59:35.395 --> 00:59:38.994
-Don't you see. it's madness?
-There is no other way!

442
00:59:40.899 --> 00:59:44.248
I ask only for the strength
to defend my people!

443
00:59:45.860 --> 00:59:48.319
-If you would but lend me the ring...
-No!

444
00:59:48.320 --> 00:59:50.969
Why do you recoil? I am no thief!

445
00:59:51.113 --> 00:59:53.162
You are not yourself!

446
00:59:54.865 --> 00:59:57.564
What chance do you think you have?

447
00:59:58.076 --> 00:59:59.909
They will find you!

448
00:59:59.910 --> 01:00:02.109
They will take the ring!

449
01:00:03.037 --> 01:00:06.086
And you will beg for death
before the end!

450
01:00:09.040 --> 01:00:10.489
You fool!

451
01:00:11.542 --> 01:00:13.376
It is not your save
by unhappy chance

452
01:00:13.377 --> 01:00:16.252
That could have been mine!
It should be mine!

453
01:00:16.252 --> 01:00:17.951
Give it to me!

454
01:00:18.753 --> 01:00:19.902
No!

455
01:00:19.921 --> 01:00:20.337
Give me the ring!

456
01:00:20.338 --> 01:00:21.487
No!

457
01:00:29.593 --> 01:00:31.342
I see your mind

458
01:00:31.553 --> 01:00:34.202
You will take the ring to Sauron!

459
01:00:34.720 --> 01:00:36.669
You will betray us!

460
01:00:36.930 --> 01:00:40.179
You go to your death.
and the death of us all!

461
01:00:40.432 --> 01:00:41.558
Curse you!

462
01:00:41.559 --> 01:00:42.349
Curse you!

463
01:00:42.350 --> 01:00:44.449
And all the halflings!

464
01:00:51.106 --> 01:00:52.405
Frodo?

465
01:00:57.108 --> 01:00:58.407
Frodo?

466
01:01:00.610 --> 01:01:02.409
I must find him!

467
01:01:04.696 --> 01:01:06.345
Please. Frodo

468
01:01:06.406 --> 01:01:08.305
Frodo. I'm sorry!!

469
01:01:57.809 --> 01:01:59.108
Frodo?

470
01:02:00.561 --> 01:02:01.977
It has taken Boromir

471
01:02:01.978 --> 01:02:03.728
Where is the ring?

472
01:02:03.729 --> 01:02:05.228
Stay away!

473
01:02:09.858 --> 01:02:11.816
I swore to protect you!

474
01:02:11.816 --> 01:02:14.515
Can you protect me from yourself?!

475
01:02:23.282 --> 01:02:25.331
Would you destroy it?

476
01:02:35.914 --> 01:02:37.413
Aragorn...

477
01:02:39.999 --> 01:02:41.498
Elessar...

478
01:02:49.546 --> 01:02:52.395
I would have gone with you to the end

479
01:02:54.049 --> 01:02:56.498
Into the very fires of Mordor

480
01:02:59.677 --> 01:03:00.976
I know

481
01:03:03.387 --> 01:03:05.486
Look after the others.

482
01:03:05.597 --> 01:03:07.346
Especially Sam.

483
01:03:07.515 --> 01:03:09.614
he will not understand

484
01:03:11.934 --> 01:03:13.433
Go. Frodo!

485
01:03:16.770 --> 01:03:17.969
Run!

486
01:03:19.146 --> 01:03:20.345
RUN!

487
01:03:45.745 --> 01:03:47.294
Mr. Frodo?!

488
01:03:56.638 --> 01:03:57.848
Find the Halflings!

489
01:03:57.849 --> 01:03:59.798
Find the Halflings!

490
01:04:13.293 --> 01:04:14.892
Aragorn. go!

491
01:04:34.872 --> 01:04:36.271
Elendil!

492
01:04:37.376 --> 01:04:38.675
Frodo!

493
01:04:38.962 --> 01:04:40.811
Hide here! Quick!

494
01:04:41.258 --> 01:04:42.657
Come on!

495
01:04:45.182 --> 01:04:46.981
What's he doing?

496
01:04:51.484 --> 01:04:53.133
He's leaving!

497
01:04:58.163 --> 01:04:59.312
No!

498
01:05:05.802 --> 01:05:07.551
Run. Frodo. Go!

499
01:05:09.140 --> 01:05:11.184
Hey. hey you! Over here!

500
01:05:11.185 --> 01:05:13.934
Over here! Hey!
Over here! This way!

501
01:05:25.168 --> 01:05:28.167
-It's working!
-I know it's working! Run!

502
01:06:16.842 --> 01:06:18.791
The horn of Gondor!

503
01:06:19.138 --> 01:06:20.537
Boromir!

504
01:06:44.807 --> 01:06:46.106
Go!
Go!

505
01:10:10.669 --> 01:10:11.670
They took the little ones!

506
01:10:11.671 --> 01:10:12.880
Be still!

507
01:10:12.881 --> 01:10:15.030
Frodo?!
Where is Frodo?!

508
01:10:17.764 --> 01:10:19.463
I let Frodo go

509
01:10:20.102 --> 01:10:22.551
Then you did what I could not

510
01:10:23.149 --> 01:10:25.798
I tried to take the ring from him

511
01:10:27.532 --> 01:10:30.131
The ring is beyond our reach now

512
01:10:30.370 --> 01:10:31.872
Forgive me!

513
01:10:31.873 --> 01:10:33.672
I did not see it

514
01:10:33.918 --> 01:10:35.754
I have failed you all

515
01:10:35.755 --> 01:10:37.304
No. Boromir

516
01:10:38.133 --> 01:10:40.032
You fought bravely

517
01:10:41.096 --> 01:10:43.245
You've kept your honour

518
01:10:44.311 --> 01:10:45.760
Leave it!

519
01:10:46.315 --> 01:10:47.814
It is over

520
01:10:49.528 --> 01:10:51.877
The world of men will fall.

521
01:10:52.659 --> 01:10:55.108
and all will come to darkness

522
01:10:55.164 --> 01:10:57.063
My city to ruin...

523
01:11:02.384 --> 01:11:05.263
I do not know what strength
is in my blood

524
01:11:05.264 --> 01:11:08.913
But I swear to you.
I will not let the White City fall

525
01:11:10.190 --> 01:11:12.139
Nor our people fail

526
01:11:14.155 --> 01:11:15.654
Our people

527
01:11:18.663 --> 01:11:20.212
Our people!

528
01:11:42.705 --> 01:11:45.504
I would have followed you.
my brother

529
01:11:47.087 --> 01:11:48.636
my captain.

530
01:11:51.762 --> 01:11:53.161
my King!

531
01:12:13.718 --> 01:12:15.317
Be at peace.

532
01:12:15.930 --> 01:12:17.579
son of Gondor

533
01:12:57.127 --> 01:12:58.426
Frodo!

534
01:13:18.623 --> 01:13:21.422
I wish the ring had never come to me

535
01:13:23.089 --> 01:13:25.688
I wish none of this had happened

536
01:13:29.058 --> 01:13:31.561
So do all who live to see such times.

537
01:13:31.562 --> 01:13:34.261
but that is not for them to decide

538
01:13:35.778 --> 01:13:37.877
All you have to decide

539
01:13:38.574 --> 01:13:41.923
is what to do with the time
that is given to you

540
01:14:12.801 --> 01:14:14.094
Frodo! No!

541
01:14:14.095 --> 01:14:15.694
Frodo!
Frodo!

542
01:14:17.392 --> 01:14:18.791
No. Sam!

543
01:14:23.028 --> 01:14:24.677
Go back. Sam!

544
01:14:25.699 --> 01:14:27.326
I'm going to Mordor alone!

545
01:14:27.327 --> 01:14:29.079
Of course you are!

546
01:14:29.080 --> 01:14:31.279
And I'm coming with you!

547
01:14:32.543 --> 01:14:34.292
You can't swim!

548
01:14:38.554 --> 01:14:39.753
Sam!

549
01:14:45.651 --> 01:14:46.850
Sam!

550
01:15:27.933 --> 01:15:30.282
I made a promise. Mr. Frodo

551
01:15:31.147 --> 01:15:32.440
A promise!

552
01:15:32.441 --> 01:15:35.240
Don't you leave him
Samwise Gamgee...

553
01:15:36.990 --> 01:15:38.939
And I don't mean to

554
01:15:39.619 --> 01:15:41.368
I don't mean to

555
01:15:42.334 --> 01:15:43.733
Oh. Sam!

556
01:16:00.073 --> 01:16:01.672
Come on then

557
01:16:30.041 --> 01:16:31.340
Hurry!

558
01:16:31.794 --> 01:16:34.943
Frodo and Sam
have reached the eastern shore

559
01:16:49.951 --> 01:16:54.300
-You mean not to follow them
-Frodo's fate is no longer in our hands

560
01:16:58.425 --> 01:17:02.074
Then It has all been in vain
The fellowship has failed

561
01:17:15.037 --> 01:17:17.736
What if we hold true to each other

562
01:17:19.712 --> 01:17:23.511
We will not abandon Merry and Pippin
to torment and death

563
01:17:24.471 --> 01:17:28.820
Not while we have strength left!
Leave all that can be spared behind

564
01:17:31.817 --> 01:17:33.616
We travel light!

565
01:17:33.903 --> 01:17:35.902
Let's hunt some orc!

566
01:17:38.870 --> 01:17:40.469
YES! Ha. ha!

567
01:18:00.158 --> 01:18:03.357
Mordor...
I hope the others find a safer road

568
01:18:05.917 --> 01:18:08.316
Strider will look after them

569
01:18:09.674 --> 01:18:12.723
I don't suppose we'll ever see them again

570
01:18:13.222 --> 01:18:15.721
We may yet. Mr. Frodo
We may...

571
01:18:19.108 --> 01:18:20.257
Sam

572
01:18:23.950 --> 01:18:26.149
I'm glad you're with me.

573
01:18:27.305 --> 01:19:27.607
